@database epsffit.guide

@width 72

@node main "epsffit.guide"

PSUtils Release 1 Patchlevel 16

NAME

epsffit - fit encapsulated PostScript file (EPSF) into constrained size


SYNOPSIS

@{b}epsffit@{ub} [@{b}-c@{ub}] [@{b}-r@{ub}] [@{b}-a@{ub}] [@{b}-m@{ub}] [@{b}-s@{ub}] @{i}"llx lly urx ury" @{ui}[@{i}infile@{ui} [@{i}outfile@{ui}] ]


DESCRIPTION

@{i}Epsffit@{ui} fits an EPSF file (encapsulated PostScript) to a given
bounding box.  The coordinates of the box are given by @{i}(llx,lly) @{ui}for the
lower left, and @{i}(urx,ury) @{ui}for the upper right, in PostScript
units (points).

If no input or output files are specified, @{i}epsffit @{ui}read from the
standard input and writes to the standard output.


OPTIONS

@{b}-c@{ub} Center the image in the given bounding box.

@{b}-r@{ub} Rotate the image by 90 degrees counter-clockwise.

@{b}-a@{ub} Adjust the aspect ratio to fit the bounding box. The default
is to preserve the aspect ratio.

@{b}-m@{ub} Rotates the image to maximise the size if it would fit the
specified bounding box better.

@{b}-s@{ub} Add a @{i}showpage @{ui}at the end of the file to force the
image to print.


